The paper discusses the design, implementation, security analysis, and evaluation of distributed, privacy-preserving, and end-to-end verifiable e-voting systems. This involves topics such as cryptography, distributed systems, information theory, and software engineering, which are covered by the sub-categories cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.DC, cs.IT, and cs.SE.
